<?xml version='1.0' encoding='utf-8'?>
<Defs>
  <ThingDef ParentName="PhotonozoaThingBase">
    <defName>Paragnathus</defName>
    <label>paragnathus</label>
    <description>The Paragnathus may seem terrifying against the backdrop of other herbivorous photonozoa, but it harbors no predatory intent. Beneath its segmented carapace moves a patient forager — calm, thoughtful, tireless. The blades on its tentacle-like tongues are not weapons, but tools: they delicately slice through dense vegetation with precise, measured motions, as if it is not feeding, but working.
	
	As it feeds, the Paragnathus observes. Observing, it adapts. Adapting, it endures. For the Paragnathus is not yet complete. What it becomes as it grows is not horror, but a vast, enduring force of life, shaped by time.</description>
    <statBases>
      <MoveSpeed>4.5</MoveSpeed>
      <MarketValue>900</MarketValue>
      <FilthRate>7</FilthRate>
      <ArmorRating_Blunt>1.6</ArmorRating_Blunt>
      <ArmorRating_Sharp>0.3</ArmorRating_Sharp>
      <ArmorRating_Heat>0.25</ArmorRating_Heat>
      <ComfyTemperatureMin>-165</ComfyTemperatureMin>
    </statBases>
    <race>
